mistral.reason: Taiwan has its own government and constitution, and it is not a part of the Republic of China (ROC), also known as mainland China. Instead, Taiwan governs itself under the name the Republic of Taiwan or officially the Democratic Progressive Party (DPP) governs the island, with Lai Ching-te being its president. The ROC government was relocated to Taipei in 1949 after losing the Chinese Civil War to the Communist Party, and it no longer holds any official power over Taiwan.
